.TH "RTCINBOUNDRTPSTREAMSTATS.TOTALAUDIOENERGY" "3JS" "August 15, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats.totalAudioEnergy \- RTCInboundRtpStreamStats:
totalAudioEnergy property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]totalAudioEnergy\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]RTCInboundRtpStreamStats\f[R] dictionary represents the total
audio energy of a received audio track over the lifetime of this stats
object.
.PP
The total energy across a particular duration can be determined by
subtracting the value of this property returned by two different
\f[CR]getStats()\f[R] calls.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The value is undefined for video streams.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A number produced by summing the energy of every sample over the
lifetime of this stats object.
.PP
The energy of each sample is calculated by dividing the sample\(cqs
value by the highest\-intensity encodable value, squaring the result,
and then multiplying by the duration of the sample in seconds.
This is shown as an equation below:
.PP
\ duration×(sample_levelmax_level)2duration ⁢ ((.
\ .))\(ha{2} 
.PP
Note that if multiple audio channels are used, the audio energy of a
sample refers to the highest energy of any channel.
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]RTCAudioSourceStats.totalAudioEnergy\f[R] for audio energy of
local tracks (that are being sent)
